  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable, org.eclipse.core.runtime.IExecutableExtension, org.eclipse.ui.IPersistable, org.eclipse.ui.IViewPart, org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchPart, org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchPart2, org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchPart3, org.eclipse.ui.part.IWorkbenchPartOrientation

    public class FlowsWorkflow
extends org.eclipse.ui.part.ViewPart
    The Flows Workflow is the first example of a workflow in the Harmonization Tool. In the future, there will be many workflows that users can utilize. The first operation that the user will perform once the Harmonization Tool is running and they have selected their working directories resides within the window produced in this class. The window is called the Inventory Workflow (the window name can be found within the plugin.xml file).

    ttransue
